qas.question: What island did Great Britain lose in 1756?

answers.text: Great Britain lost Minorca in the Mediterranean to the French in 1756

qas.question: What possession did the French lose to the Brits in 1758

answers.text: captured the French colonies in Senegal in 1758

qas.question: Identify the French colonies lost  to the British in 1759 and 1762.

answers.text: The British Royal Navy took the French sugar colonies of Guadeloupe in 1759 and Martinique in 1762

qas.question: What success did the British have in Cuba?

answers.text: Spanish cities of Havana in Cuba

qas.question: What other colony was taken by the British from Spain?

context: <a0_0>Great Britain lost Minorca in the Mediterranean to the French in 1756<a0_0/> but <a1_0>captured the French colonies in Senegal in 1758<a1_0/>. <a2_0>The British Royal Navy took the French sugar colonies of Guadeloupe in 1759 and Martinique in 1762<a2_0/> as well as the <a3_0>Spanish cities of Havana in Cuba<a3_0/>, and <a4_0>Manila in the Philippines<a4_0/>, both prominent Spanish colonial cities. However, expansion into the hinterlands of both cities met with stiff resistance. In the Philippines, the British were confined to Manila until their agreed upon withdrawal at the war's end.
